7.11	Khokhloma	Khokhloma	Khokhloma or Khokhloma painting (Хохлома, Хохломская роспись in Russian, or Khokhlomskaya rospis') is the name of a Russian wood painting handicraft style, known for its vivid flower patterns, red and gold colors over a black background, and the distinctive effect it has when applied to cheap and light wooden tableware or furniture, making it look heavier, metal-like, and glamorous.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b8/1979_CPA_4968.jpg/220px-1979_CPA_4968.jpg
